  "texts": [
    "That said, these connections between emotional responses and improved outcomes were generally weaker than the connections between emotions and specific emotional experiences.",
    "Participants' immediate emotional reactions, as captured by concepts such as 'sad', 'delighted', and 'irritated', were more prominent in the data, reflecting the varied and often conflicting feelings participants had about using AI-generated feedback.",
    "Participants expressed a range of feelings regarding their motivation after receiving feedback, reflecting a mix of reactions.",
    "Some participants described the motivational effect of the feedback as mild, suggesting that while it provided some encouragement, it was not particularly inspiring.",
    "Others were more enthusiastic, explaining that the feedback gave them a sense of purpose and transformed an otherwise monotonous task into something more meaningful."
